# Lenovo Zero-Floor — scoped agent rule

This rule applies **only** when the task explicitly targets **Lenovo Zero-Floor** or **`[data-theme="lenovo"]`** UI. The default Agentic theme (`color-semantic.json`) is unchanged for other work.

## Read first

- [`design-system/tokens/lenovo-zero-floor.md`](design-system/tokens/lenovo-zero-floor.md) — brand rules, theme switching, CSS map
- [`design-system/tokens/color-semantic-lenovo.json`](design-system/tokens/color-semantic-lenovo.json) — light semantics
- [`design-system/tokens/typography-lenovo.json`](design-system/tokens/typography-lenovo.json) — font stacks; weights **400 / 500 / 700 only** (no `font-semibold` / 600)
- [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) §2 — full document index

## Non-negotiables

- **No hardcoded colors** — CSS variables or semantic tokens from the Lenovo files above. See also [`.cursor/rules/tokens-css.mdc`](tokens-css.mdc): each token maps to the **correct CSS property** (e.g. font-size tokens on `font-size`, not Tailwind `text-*` for size).
- **Purple primary** — CTAs, focus rings, info accents; use `semantic.primary.*` / `--color-interactive-primary` (or aliased `--color-primary` in Storybook CSS).
- **Red only** for destructive actions, error feedback, invalid fields, and **Lenovo logo** — never for links, nav, or generic interactive states. Do not use `red-*` / `rose-*` / `pink-*` Tailwind for interactive UI.
- **Success = on-brand blue** in Lenovo (`semantic.success.*`), not green — differs from default theme.
- **Icons:** still **Material Design only** per [`design-system/policies/iconography.md`](design-system/policies/iconography.md).
- **Accessibility:** still WCAG 2.2 AA per [`design-system/policies/accessibility.md`](design-system/policies/accessibility.md) and `.cursor/rules/accessibility.mdc`.

## Implementation

- Load Lenovo CSS variables from [`design-system/css/design-tokens-lenovo.css`](design-system/css/design-tokens-lenovo.css) (after `design-system/css/design-tokens.css`) under `[data-theme="lenovo"]`.
- **Dark Lenovo:** [`color-semantic-dark-lenovo.json`](design-system/tokens/color-semantic-dark-lenovo.json) is **provisional** — verify contrast before shipping.

Do not duplicate long hex tables in generated code; reference tokens and the CSS file so values stay single-sourced.
